<text id="02-output-contract" title="Secrets Management Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="900" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema (draft-07) for the artefact this methodology produces, plus one valid and one invalid example, and a closed list of forbidden patterns the validator must reject.</summary>

  <section title="JSON Schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/secrets-management.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "artefact_id",
    "version",
    "last_reviewed",
    "secrets",
    "consumers",
    "owner"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "artefact_id": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "version": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$"
    },
    "last_reviewed": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date"
    },
    "secrets": {
      "type": "array"
    },
    "consumers": {
      "type": "array"
    },
    "rotation_cadence_days": {
      "type": "integer"
    },
    "owner": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "leak_response_plan": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <pattern id="f1">owner == &apos;team&apos; / &apos;we&apos; / &apos;&apos; / null.</pattern>
      <pattern id="f2">Any consumer EnvironmentFile path with mode != 0600 (per audit script).</pattern>
      <pattern id="f3">secret with no consumer (orphan).</pattern>
      <pattern id="f4">rotation_cadence_days &gt; 365 for class in [db, api_key, jwt].</pattern>
    </list>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_id": "secrets-prod-2026-q2",
  "version": "1.1.0",
  "last_reviewed": "2026-05-23",
  "secrets": [
    {
      "name": "DB_PASSWORD",
      "class": "db",
      "vault": "1Password/faion.net"
    }
  ],
  "consumers": [
    {
      "unit": "faion-net-api.service",
      "env_file": "/etc/faion-net-api.env"
    }
  ],
  "rotation_cadence_days": 90,
  "owner": "@ruslan",
  "leak_response_plan": "rotate via op, redeploy, post-mortem"
}
]]></code>
    <note>Minimum viable conformant output — every required field present, no forbidden pattern matched.</note>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "secrets": [
    {
      "name": "DB_PASSWORD"
    }
  ],
  "consumers": [],
  "owner": "team"
}
]]></code>
    <note>owner=`team` (forbidden); missing artefact_id, version, last_reviewed; consumers empty — secret with no declared consumer is unrotatable.</note>
  </example>

  <reference path="scripts/validate-secrets-management.py">Schema validator (stdlib only).</reference>
</text>
